Judgment is expected in the latest bid by Former President Jacob Zuma to have state prosecutor Billy Downer removed from his corruption trial. eNCA's Siphamandla Goge is following these developments. Courtesy #DStv403 PIETERMARITZBURG - Judgment is expected in the latest bid by former president Jacob Zuma to have state prosecutor Billy Downer removed from his corruption trial. This comes after Judge Piet Koen dismissed the application in October last year. READ: Mpofu: Zuma not responsible for delays Zuma's lawyer, Advocate Dali Mpofu, says the former president now wants the matter to go to the Supreme Court of appeal as he feels the case is being treated differently from others. eNCA senior reporter  Siphamandla  Goge is following these developments and shares more details in the video above.